BASIC LINUX COMMANDS
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
mkdir   (create directory)
cd    (change directory)
cd ..  (go to previous directory)
touch [file-name]   (make a empty file)
pwd   (current directory path)
ls    (list objects in an directory)
rmdir   (remove directory)
rm   (remove file)
cat   (get contents of a file)
echo  (print to console)
man  (show manual)
whoami  (who's the current user)
clear   (clear the console screen)
history   (show all commands history)
cp [current] [destination]  (copy a file to destinationn)
mv [current] [destination]   (move a file to destination)
mv [old-name] [new-name]   (change the name of a file)
